# OmniBus Node (C++20) - Complete Implementation

Third sibling implementation of the OmniBus blockchain, fully wire‑compatible and chain‑compatible with the Zig (`core/`) and Rust (`core-rust/`) nodes.

## Features

- ✅ **Full node** implementation - no stubs, all functionality complete
- ✅ **Wire-compatible** P2P protocol (HELLO/WELCOME/STABLE handshake)
- ✅ **Chain-compatible** - identical block hashes and chain.dat format
- ✅ **Native bech32 addresses** with HRP `ob`
- ✅ **EVM compatibility** (chain ID 7771)
- ✅ **DEX with price-time priority matching**
- ✅ **Post-quantum cryptography** (ML-DSA-87, Falcon-512, SLH-DSA-256s, ML-KEM-768)
- ✅ **Validator staking** with 5 tiers (100 to 500,000 OMNI)
- ✅ **Governance** with proposals and voting
- ✅ **Identity system** (DID, KYC, MiCA reporting, Name Service)
- ✅ **Light client** support with SPV and Bloom filters
- ✅ **Mining** with stratum pool support
- ✅ **WebSocket** events (17 event types)
- ✅ **RPC** (native + Ethereum JSON-RPC)

## Building

```bash
./scripts/build.sh